name: JRNL LG (red + kraft)
description:
Large journals made from printer's remnant papers, vintage ledger paper and gummed canning labels. The cover is made from vintage kraft colored file folders. The inside pages are a smooth ivory. End papers are vintage ledger paper I picked up while traveling and the back page is finished with a stash pocket. Limited Edition of 13.

Size 8.5 x 5.5" 
48 pages

name: JRNL LG (blue + suede)
description:
Large journals made from printer's remnant papers, vintage graph paper and gummed canning labels. The cover is made from a paper called SuedeTex that feels like a real leather and is incredibly durable. The inside pages are made from French Paper Co. retired light blue paper with white flecks. End papers are vintage graph paper and the back page is finished with a stash pocket. Limited Edition of 30.

Size 8.5 x 5.5"
48 pages

name: JRNL SML
description:
Pocket sized journals made from rescued file folders, vintage graph paper, printer remnant paper and an old gummed label. The inside paper is an ecru with a cockle finish. 48 pages total, the back 24 are perforated so you can easily remove them. Finished with a stash pocket in the back. Limited Edition of 85.

This journal comes in five options, choose your favorite.

Size 5x4"

name: Grids & Lines Note set
description:
My vintage office paper supply got a little out of hand so I decided to make my stacks into note sets. Paired with a hard working kraft envelope, these note sets will make you feel scholarly. 

Set of six with assorted papers. White address labels included.

3.5" x 5" folded

name: TO labels
description:
These labels are designed after vintage gummed canning and mailing labels. Offset printed in dense red ink on hefty kraft colored label stock. Self adhesive. Packaged in assorted small floral envelopes.
 
1 5/8 x 2 1/2"

set of 12

name: Neon Flower Power Notes
description:
These Florescent mod envelopes are even more psychedelic in person. Screenprinted in florescent orange, pink and yellow they abound with day-glow cheer. The front of the envelope is unprinted golden yellow and I'm pairing these groovy envelopes with a cool jadeite flat card. 

*Please note the actual envelopes are much brighter than the picture can show. True florescent/day-glow/neon colors in person.

Limited edition of 15

4 1/8 x 5 3/4"

name: Flower Girl Vintage Notes
description:
I picked up these delightful vintage envelopes at an antique mall. They are offset printed in bright colors that have somehow maintained their brilliance over the last forty or more years. I paired them with vintage index cards that happened to be the exact size and also featured bright hues of pink and blue. Both the cards and the envelopes are old and show some signs of aging. 

4 1/8 x 6 1/4"

name: Jam Cards
description:
This micro edition features vintage canning labels and cookbook illustrations sewn to blank recipe cards. Perfect notecard for gifting your handmade sweets or for a keen hostess. Please choose by flavor, each card is handmade and will vary ever so slightly.

name: Hello Guest Note Set
description:
I love writing notes and invoices up on these charming old diner receipt pads. Recently I discovered an envelope in a perfect brown kraft, that fits them like a glove! (I have a thing against ill fitting envelopes, it's a weakness.) This set comes with two lightweight sheets and one ungummed envelope. You will have to get crafty with a gluestick, washi tape or a fancy wax seal to close. Each is rubber stamped with the word "HELLO" at top in red. 

3 3/4 x 5 1/2"

Custom imprinting available, please leave me a note in the shopping cart.

name: HI cards
description:
These anytime cards are inspired by school notebooks and teacher ledgers. The envelopes are converted from old pads of ledger paper I've collected through the years. These foldover cards are locally offset printed in two spot colors. Paired with a vintage inspired mailing label and simple grey wafer seal.

name: Bookmarks

One-of-a-kind bookmarks featuring vintage book art stitched to brown cardstock. Tiny bookplate on back provides space for personalization or note.

name: Heart Key
description: Skeleton keys laser cut from vintage picture book covers. Paired with a small manila envelope that reads "to my heart" across the front, a small blank card to write a note, and a little foil heart to seal it. 2" x 3.5" As featured in "1,000 Handmade Greetings".

name: Black Rainbow
description:
Exploring the "somewhere" over the rainbow. 

I made these prints this past summer at art camp in Vermont. Carved rubber stamp printed on 3"x4" vintage note paper with a felt finish. Hand printed - variations will occur.

Signed and dated on verso.
Limited Edition, unnumbered.

name: Self Portrait (with fever)
description: I met Angela around the world at an art camp in Sweden in 2011. This past summer I had the pleasure of her company again at a reunion. Unfortunately for Angela, she found herself trapped in bed with a fever at camp, but fortunately for us she made this haunting drawing in her sketch book. This print is a two spot color lithograph on recycled paper 8"x10" Signed, numbered and illustrated by Angela Corti for Art School Girl. Inspired by life and it's colors, Argentinian artist Angela Corti uses texture and line in a constant search for the union of art and design. SEDUCIDA POR LA VIDA Y SUS COLORES, COMBINA TEXTURAS, COLLAGES Y LINEA NEGRA EN UNA BÚSQUEDA CONSTANTE DE UNIÓN ENTRE EL ARTE Y EL DISEÑO.

A charming piece of functional wall art. Metal ring binding and nail hole for hanging. 4.25" x 11.5" see all images here

name: Fika + Farewell
description: This past summer I had the pleasure of studying in Sweden with the talented Miss Camilla Engman. I made this print in response to my trip for the generous souls who helped fund my trip via Kickstarter. Fika is a break that Swedes take at any time of the day that commonly involves a friend, some coffee and something sweet. While on an outing one of the ladies in our group ordered a peculiar dessert resembling a meatball. It was a chocolate ball or “chokladbollar”, a very simple and common Swedish dessert. Chocolate balls quickly became a favorite treat for everyone,as well as the subject of paintings and drawings. At our farewell dinner on Camilla’s studio rooftop we were greeted by a hand shaped hot air balloon floating over head. A symbol of our impending farewell. This print is a combination of a block print and a Gocco screenprint printed by hand in my studio. Because they are hand inked, each one varies in color and texture. See detailed photos.

description: Title: Mr. Rx Nako Okubo spent much of her early education hand drawing "typefaces" instead of listening to her teachers. Not surprisingly, she now gets paid to make things look good for a huge spectrum of clients from fortune 500 companies to neighborhood nonprofits. The one-time go-go dancer feels inspired by powerlines, fluorescents, registration marks and—you might have guessed—kids' handwriting. name: ASG Ed. #8 - Molly Carter
description: Title: Mary Combining traditional femininity and the allure of fashion with an examination of the grotesque and technical, Molly Carter's work is at once beautiful and unsettling. Finding inspiration at opposite ends of the spectrum, her work references the classic female experience (makeup counters, dress forms, fabric + thread) and the science of architectural renderings, prosthetic limbs and the cataloging of museum specimens. Molly lives and works in Rockford, Illinois, with her husband (ASG Ed. #4 artist David Menard) and their two young boys.
